-- RBS Will Close Its German M&A Operations, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-05-31T06:46:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/rbs-will-close-its-german-m-a-operations-handelsblatt-reports.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc  will
close down its German mergers and acquisitions division, which
employs almost 20 people, to focus on its existing business with
some 150 corporate clients in the country,  Handelsblatt  reported
today, citing Ingrid Hengster, head of the German unit of RBS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
